==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Creance
<hw>Cre"ance</hw> <pr>(kr⟦emac⟧"<it>a</it>ns)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[F. <ets>cr⟦eacute⟧ance</ets>, lit., credence, fr. L.
<ets>credere</ets> to trust. See <er>Credence</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Faith; belief; creed.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Falconry)</fld> <def>A fine, small line, fastened
to a hawk's leash, when it is first lured.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Creance</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Creance
<hw>Cre"ance</hw> <pr>(kr⟦emac⟧"<it>a</it>ns)</pr>, <pos>v. i. &
t.</pos> <def>To get on credit; to borrow.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
